Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.34,0:00:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you bastards doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.60,0:00:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Iron Body!\N--Hm? You son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.40,0:00:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blueno! What's the meaning of...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.74,0:00:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What's this? How cocky...!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.66,0:00:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think I am?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.20,0:01:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you trying to pick a fight with?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.50,0:01:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're only a dull bar owner!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.71,0:01:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up with that getup?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.96,0:01:16.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem different from your usual self!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.18,0:01:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.30,0:01:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't, Blueno.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.23,0:01:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! A-Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.82,0:01:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hang in there!\N--We can't kill him yet. Don't forget our mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.61,0:01:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Sorry.\N--Wh-Wh-What's going on?! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.53,0:01:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I saw them working at the shipyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell? Why was he able to...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.62,0:01:45.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastards! What are you people?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.96,0:01:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are acting pretty super, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.58,0:01:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you hurt innocent girls?!\NThey're like my little sisters, you jerks!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.05,0:01:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To start with, how the hell\Ndo you know about this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.38,0:01:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my secret base!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.05,0:02:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't care about that. I'll keep\Nthis simple. Listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.52,0:02:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our lives in this town were a cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.14,0:02:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In reality, we are World\NGovernment intelligence agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must know what that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.65,0:02:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...as well as the reason we came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.99,0:02:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franky... we already know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.03,0:02:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cutty Flam...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.03,0:02:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom's other disciple, who was said\Nto have died eight years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.13,0:02:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how you found\Nthat out... but that's splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.67,0:02:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, I'm starting to feel uneasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.34,0:02:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that idiot Iceberg doing okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.68,0:02:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:54.69,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.15,0:02:58.65,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.65,0:03:01.99,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,As power passes through our clasped hands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:05.66,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.96,0:03:20.67,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Working together, let's ride the giant waves
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.67,0:03:28.02,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry toward the excitement--\Nthere's the starting signal
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.02,0:03:34.94,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time to set sail-- let's raise anchor
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:42.07,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut through the rainbow-colored wind\Nand head for a sea of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.07,0:03:45.45,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a journey fraught with injury
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:49.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but what you cherish most will be right there
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.41,0:03:53.42,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you get into a jam
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.42,0:03:56.46,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always be there to protect you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.46,0:04:00.63,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.63,0:04:04.18,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.18,0:04:07.18,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If a storm hits, let's put\Nour arms around each other
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.18,0:04:11.48,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and gaze at the light beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.48,0:04:15.40,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we gather up the pieces of our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.40,0:04:18.69,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll make a map leading to tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:21.65,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.65,0:04:27.45,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,under the same flag-- together, we're one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:30.08,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,One Piece
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.29,0:04:46.34,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"Franky's Past! The Day\Nthe Sea Train First Ran"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.05,0:04:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try to play innocent now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...as we already know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.68,0:04:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a matter of time before I get targeted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.15,0:05:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the island with them... Franky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.61,0:05:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom handed them down to Iceberg...\Nand Iceberg to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you, come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.53,0:05:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna entrust something\Nimportant to you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.49,0:05:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mission took quite a while,\Nbut it's finally checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, hand over the blueprints for the\Nancient weapon Pluton, Cutty Flam.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.76,0:05:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flam...? That's a strange name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Franky" would do, right? "Franky" would.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.51,0:05:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.01,0:05:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.06,0:05:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying hand them over to us, Cutty Flam.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.23,0:05:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got nothing I could give you jerks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.98,0:05:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What just happened?! It was so\Nfast that I couldn't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.41,0:05:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.71,0:06:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Lucci?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.72,0:06:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this filthy room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A drafting room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.31,0:06:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.02,0:06:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a good place to hide blueprints. Find them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are... nameplates?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:33.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cutty Flam.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.66,0:06:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare touch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.80,0:06:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't intrude upon someone's memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is where we grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.22,0:06:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The shipbuilding company, Tom's Workers!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.56,0:07:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's where the world's best shipwright lived!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:08.24,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,1000)}"Water Seven, 22 years ago"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.75,0:07:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gonna eat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.96,0:07:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take these!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move! Move aside, Iceberg!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.07,0:07:51.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...! What the hell are you doing, Franky?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.12,0:08:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...! What the hell are you doing\Ninstead of helping me with work?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.91,0:08:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that you keep\Nmaking unstable stuff like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.04,0:08:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! It's none of\Nyour business, Stupid-berg!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my precious battleship,\Nthe Battle Franky!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.47,0:08:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what that is, but ditch the\Nwhole thing before someone gets hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the scrap heap island! It's my\Nown business to keep whatever I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait and see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.14,0:08:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time for sure, I'll build a\Nbattleship that will beat Sea Kings!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...! There's no way you can\Nbeat them! I hope you get eaten!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I can beat them!\N--Well...! You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.69,0:08:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I can!\N--Well...! You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're a man... do it resolutely!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That concludes the launch ceremony!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:09:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were resolutely able\Nto make a solid, good ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.68,0:09:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Yokozuna?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.77,0:09:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit! Ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.56,0:09:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's finish it up tomorrow, shall we?\NNow, let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.60,0:09:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.98,0:09:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.65,0:09:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ribbit, ribbit!\N--I wonder what we're having for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:17.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait up, Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.83,0:09:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So which Battle Franky did\Nyou build this time, Franky?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.08,0:09:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The eighth one! It was close!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.63,0:09:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.71,0:09:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... Since you let him do this stuff,\NTom-san, he gets full of himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.63,0:09:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All he makes are weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, Stupid-berg!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.76,0:09:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say, Moron-ky?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.69,0:09:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Now, now, stop fighting, both of you.\N--He said "Moron-ky"!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.69,0:09:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kokoro-san! This idiot was...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.03,0:09:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.11,0:09:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Tom-san. You're laughing\Ntoo hard. What was so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.11,0:10:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... yeah... I just remembered...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.95,0:10:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that another trading ship with\Nlumber on it was attacked by pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.83,0:10:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the King of the Pirates was executed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.41,0:10:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the number of pirates grew considerably.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.75,0:10:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all over for this town. It's being\Novertaken by the pirate era.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.96,0:10:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People are in low spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.21,0:10:26.85,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,"Merchant"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.01,0:10:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can now get lumber and iron
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only from other islands due to\Nthe floods caused by Aqua Laguna,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.06,0:10:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and yet, violent seas and pirates hinder trading.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.85,0:10:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shipyards scramble for customers\Ndue to the shortage of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.40,0:10:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They start fighting. They lose their jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If nothing is done, Water Seven,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an island that once left its mark\Nwith its shipbuilding business,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.45,0:10:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will become weak-minded,\Njust waiting for floods to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.33,0:10:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Tom-san built\Nan incredible pirate ship, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, teach me how to draw\Nblueprints for a pirate ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.46,0:10:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franky, there's no such thing\Nas blueprints for a pirate ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.55,0:11:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the sailors who board a ship put up\Na skull flag, then it's a pirate ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.35,0:11:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they put up a seagull flag,\Nthen it's a Navy ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care what you wanna build,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but a man should be resolutely\Nproud of the ship he built!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to bed yet, Tom-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.53,0:11:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you drawing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.87,0:11:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm... It's this island's hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.12,0:11:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.08,0:11:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hopefully, it can revive Water Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.17,0:11:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.42,0:11:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.56,0:11:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.28,0:12:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Government's Judicial Ship is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's a Judicial Ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a mobile court.\NWho did they come to judge?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.54,0:12:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a sec! What did\NTom-san do to deserve this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.79,0:12:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Outta my way, you jerks!\NGive us Tom-san back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.09,0:12:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.14,0:12:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san! Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.77,0:12:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The King of Pirates, Gold Roger,\Nwas executed the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We consider shipbuilding engineer Tom's\Nact of building Gold Roger's pirate ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.40,0:12:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Oro Jackson, to be aiding and\Nabetting this vicious world-class criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.82,0:12:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hence, Tom will be taken to\NEnies Lobby to be executed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.50,0:12:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.51,0:13:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is terrible! Tom will...\NTom will be executed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say it's on the charge of\Nbuilding the King of the Pirates' ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.10,0:13:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's finally time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.15,0:13:21.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It caused problems for the\Nentire world. They had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.90,0:13:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, no matter whom a shipwright\Nsells a ship to, it's not a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.61,0:13:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the King of\Nthe Pirates is an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.37,0:13:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We consider all those who have\Nassisted in his pirating activities
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.45,0:13:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to be dangerous individuals!\NHence, he's sentenced to the death penalty!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.12,0:13:39.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take the offender away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.63,0:13:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Now, let's go.\N--Hurry up and walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.71,0:13:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What's the matter?\N--Go already!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.17,0:13:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.51,0:13:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm currently designing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.85,0:13:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a paddle steamer that resolutely runs\Non a railway set on the ocean's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.10,0:13:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey! What're you saying?!\N--Why, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.06,0:14:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suppose this island's decline is due\Nto trade not happening as we wish it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.24,0:14:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suppose the hopelessness that people feel
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.61,0:14:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is coming from the worries\Nabout this sinking island...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.41,0:14:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Putting a sea train into operation...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.54,0:14:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...will definitely save Water Seven someday!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.84,0:14:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry! We'll take him out right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.34,0:14:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.84,0:14:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sea train, you said?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.43,0:14:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a ship that puffs smoke
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.51,0:14:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and runs from one island\Nto another on a sea railway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.43,0:14:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll carry people and goods as well as ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.56,0:14:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without having to worry about the weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everyone will be able to freely cross the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.73,0:14:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop kidding yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.15,0:14:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A railway? It'd be destroyed\Nonce Aqua Laguna comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.32,0:14:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Besides, there are\Nalso Sea Kings in the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea railway doesn't have to be fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.83,0:15:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll sway a little below the surface of\Nthe water, never resisting the waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.58,0:15:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if pulling in a rope, the sea train\Nwill just use the railway as a guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.76,0:15:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, I'm thinking of adding\Na mechanism that generates
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.09,0:15:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a discordant sound that fish hate\Nbetween the paddles and the railway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.47,0:15:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Sea Kings won't come close to the railway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something like that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.06,0:15:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we connect St. Poplar, Pucci,\NSan Faldo, and this island,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.36,0:15:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,industries can grow through trading.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.28,0:15:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.20,0:15:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blueprints will be completed soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.45,0:15:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's not so simple that\Nordinary shipwrights can build it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.12,0:15:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible to connect Enies Lobby as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.46,0:15:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once this technology is completed\Nand eventually crosses the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.71,0:15:50.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the relationships among islands all\Naround the world will resolutely change!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.55,0:15:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea train is the hope of Water Seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.93,0:15:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long will it take?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.30,0:15:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.76,0:15:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then build it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.93,0:16:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the development period for the sea train,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.31,0:16:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I give ten years probation\Nto shipbuilding engineer Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.23,0:16:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.99,0:16:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.95,0:16:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please save Water Seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.49,0:16:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm resolutely still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.25,0:16:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no laughing matter, Tom-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.54,0:16:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that your time had come\Nand I got a chill down my spine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.33,0:16:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But anyway, if things go well, they may\Nlet the matter with Roger go, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.34,0:16:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...! At any rate, you're great, Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.67,0:16:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that you've been\Nthinking about something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.93,0:16:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone was overwhelmed!\NThe sea train really is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.35,0:16:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the dinner! Come, Yokozuna!\NI'll teach you how to do the front crawl!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.85,0:16:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Franky! What's with you?!\NYou've been sulking for a while now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.81,0:16:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! I'm angry at everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.73,0:16:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold Roger's ship is the only ship in the\Nworld that went around the Grand Line!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.99,0:16:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does Tom-san, who built such\Na great ship, have to get executed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.91,0:17:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people there were also\Nsaying that it was just natural,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.37,0:17:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even though those idiots can't even build a raft!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.41,0:17:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also know that the reason\Nour company is under a bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.79,0:17:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is because you were kicked out by the\Ntownspeople over Roger's ship, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.75,0:17:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the hell does the world's best\Nshipwright have to be treated like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.59,0:17:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's funny, you horned raccoon dog?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.84,0:17:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who're you taking it out on, Moron-ky?!\NYou are not gonna get away with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.47,0:17:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand that the person\Nhimself is like that, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.64,0:17:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stroke with all your might\Nto push the water backwards!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.07,0:17:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit! Ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! No! Stroke more vigorously like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.20,0:17:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ribbit!\N--No! Like this!\N--Seriously, what's with him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.33,0:17:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should just kick out an idiot like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.74,0:17:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, don't say that. He's a fellow shipbuilder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.41,0:17:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In terms of shipbuilding skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.96,0:17:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's already no big difference between\Nhim and the craftsmen on the island....
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...though what he makes is shaky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.71,0:17:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's just always honest, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.93,0:18:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, when I saw a kid who had\Nresolutely appeared on the scrap heap island
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.73,0:18:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,make a cannon using junk,\NI was really surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.02,0:18:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, take me in!\NI was abandoned by my parents!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.95,0:18:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me that his parents said,\N"What an uncontrollable brat,"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.03,0:18:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and threw him off the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that they were worthless\Npirates from some place, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.50,0:18:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That was so funny!\N--Tom-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.21,0:18:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's tough, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.79,0:18:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite his circumstances, he isn't crooked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.67,0:18:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two will definitely become world-class\Nshipbuilding engineers someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.42,0:18:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be nice to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.30,0:18:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franky can't do it. He's crazy\Neven at the cellular level!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.14,0:18:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, as soon as I finish the blueprints,\Nwe'll start building the sea train!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.23,0:18:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... but I bet he won't help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.90,0:18:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can do as he pleases!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.66,0:20:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.50,0:20:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that it was the president\Nof the No. 4 shipbuilding company.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.67,0:20:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be because of that accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.75,0:20:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since they didn't have materials, he went\Nto purchase lumber on his own ship
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.63,0:20:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and got fifty people killed on the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.43,0:20:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His shipyard is closed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:20:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How weak humans are, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.77,0:20:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really it for this island?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.48,0:21:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Did you guys hear\Nabout the scrap heap island?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.20,0:21:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom's Workers has finished\Nbuilding the sea train, you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.03,0:21:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! Does a ship like this really run?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.08,0:21:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a ship built by a criminal. It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.96,0:21:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.42,0:21:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.50,0:21:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom! You are not gonna explain?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.67,0:21:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving! Get on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.43,0:21:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.76,0:21:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The paddles are grabbing the railway!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.14,0:21:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It's moving!\N--Whoa, amazing! It's running!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.28,0:21:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Twelve years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.82,0:21:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...leaving a closed, declining town,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.58,0:21:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with worried people on board...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.17,0:22:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the sea train Puffing Tom crossed\Nthe sea for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.65,0:22:33.24,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We had a dream that day
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.24,0:22:38.08,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Our belief in ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.08,0:22:47.17,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,makes us able to cross the wildly surging ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.17,0:22:56.77,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,You're braver and more caring than anyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.77,0:23:06.94,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever depart this ship\Nand live in a different world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.94,0:23:15.66,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, we can all surely smile
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.96,0:23:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So this is a place that holds\Nyour memories with Tom, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.84,0:23:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blueprints aren't here!\NGet out of here already!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.68,0:23:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! Well, fine.\NYou're a criminal, just like Tom was.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.35,0:23:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know what'll happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.72,0:23:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know anything about Tom-san!\NDon't talk like you know everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.85,0:23:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.40,0:23:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Spandam's Scheme!\NThe Day the Sea Train Shook"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.48,0:23:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
