Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.42,0:00:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.22,0:00:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The members of CP9 have\Nfinally made themselves known.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.60,0:00:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucci, Kaku, Blueno and Kalifa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.60,0:00:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy and Zoro stood up to them\Nto put a stop to their scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.27,0:00:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Lucci, who has Cat-Cat\Nfruit powers, crushed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.69,0:00:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CP9 has found out that Franky is Cutty Flam
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.78,0:01:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and has the blueprints for\Nthe ancient weapon Pluton.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.20,0:01:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got nothing I could give you jerks!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.71,0:01:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they caught Franky,\Nwho challenged them, in the blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.09,0:01:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that was rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.93,0:01:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pay him back two times over.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.39,0:01:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not until we get what we want,\Nshipwright Cutty Flam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.56,0:01:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blueprints are not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.28,0:01:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.67,0:01:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.22,0:02:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the hell is this happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.10,0:02:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! I'd better hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.52,0:02:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Just as I planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were taken in by the Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.72,0:02:40.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're gonna make us the culprits\Nfor attacking the Judicial Ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.84,0:02:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because they want to question Tom-san\Nas a criminal to obtain the blueprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all this... can you still\Nsay that you're innocent?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.56,0:02:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't somehow stop them\Nfrom taking Tom-san away...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.11,0:02:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll never...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:03:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...forgive you for the rest of my life, Franky!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.08,0:03:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.37,0:03:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.83,0:03:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.12,0:03:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame him, Iceberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.54,0:03:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not Franky's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.05,0:03:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still saying that, even at this point?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.05,0:03:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I made this harpoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.39,0:03:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made it so that it can't come\Nout once it pierces its target!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.64,0:03:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.85,0:03:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't apologize. This is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.02,0:03:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! They're over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.86,0:03:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom is on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.40,0:03:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he seriously injured like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it wasn't them who made the raid?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.91,0:03:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The townspeople are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.75,0:03:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...shall we head to the town, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard, Spanda!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's "Spandam"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.42,0:04:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you criminals...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.80,0:04:08.68,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.14,0:04:12.64,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:15.98,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,As power passes through our clasped hands
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.98,0:04:19.65,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.95,0:04:34.67,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Working together, let's ride the giant waves
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.67,0:04:42.05,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry toward the excitement--\Nthere's the starting signal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.05,0:04:48.93,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time to set sail-- let's raise anchor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:56.06,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut through the rainbow-colored wind\Nand head for a sea of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.06,0:04:59.44,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a journey fraught with injury
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:03.40,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but what you cherish most will be right there
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:07.45,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you get into a jam
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.45,0:05:10.45,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always be there to protect you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.45,0:05:14.62,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.62,0:05:18.21,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.21,0:05:21.17,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If a storm hits, let's put\Nour arms around each other
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.17,0:05:25.51,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and gaze at the light beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.51,0:05:29.43,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we gather up the pieces of our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:32.68,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll make a map leading to tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.68,0:05:35.64,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.64,0:05:41.44,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,under the same flag-- together, we're one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.44,0:05:44.07,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,One Piece
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:06:00.04,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"The End of the Legendary Man!\NThe Day the Sea Train Cried"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.21,0:06:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the raid culprits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please rest easy, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We, CP5, brought them down\Nafter they made the raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't cause any more trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.47,0:06:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would've been found\Nnot guilty in today's trial...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.56,0:06:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, why did Tom do something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.73,0:06:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was a friend of the\NKing of the Pirates after all, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.44,0:06:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.78,0:06:27.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Spandam from CP5.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You happened to be there?\NThank you. You saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.11,0:06:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please hand them over to us,\Nas we would like to investigate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.21,0:06:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try making excuses if you like.\NOur trustworthiness is worlds apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.88,0:06:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the blueprints of the ancient weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ribbit, ribbit.\N--How terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.85,0:06:56.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, about the sea train,\Nall I can say is, splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.60,0:07:01.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see it'll contribute greatly\Nto the growth of Water Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.27,0:07:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that, on the previous charge\Nfor building Gold Roger's ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.44,0:07:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your acquittal today had\Npretty much been decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, why did you commit another crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.95,0:07:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a load of crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not the ones who\Nraided the Judicial Ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.16,0:07:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was that Spandam guy who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.67,0:07:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.21,0:07:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's got into that disciple of Tom's,\Nsuddenly cracking jokes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.84,0:07:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would CP5, a Government entity,\Ngain by sinking a Judicial Ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.97,0:07:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a stupid thing to say!\NThat's not possible at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cutty Flam, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.48,0:07:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To start with, we caught you\Nred-handed on one of the raid ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.03,0:07:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, weren't those raid\Nships built by your company?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.25,0:08:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ships that would do something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.79,0:08:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're... no longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.38,0:08:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.81,0:08:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom tore his handcuffs apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.52,0:08:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.11,0:08:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san... hit Franky for the first time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.66,0:08:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you do that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.83,0:08:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"They're no longer my ships," you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.29,0:08:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can say anything but that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.08,0:08:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with saying that?!\NI'm regretting it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.71,0:08:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only those ships didn't exist,\Nno one would have had to get hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.80,0:08:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what kind of ship it is,\Nthe act of building it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.06,0:09:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is neither an act of good nor evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care what kind of\Nships you choose to build,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.61,0:09:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but even if the ships you built hurt someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.57,0:09:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or even if they destroy the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.86,0:09:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at least the one who created\Nthem must love them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.24,0:09:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their creator mustn't deny them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.58,0:09:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame the ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.29,0:09:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man should be resolutely proud...\Nof the ships he created!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.02,0:09:50.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.06,0:09:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franky...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.02,0:09:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interfere in what I'm about to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:09:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.61,0:10:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the World Government\Nwho pinned the crime on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.58,0:10:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also the World Government who judges it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way that we'll\Nget cleared of suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.04,0:10:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.79,0:10:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be really tough for you to see\Nyour innocent ships being used like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.09,0:10:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must want to beat up\Nthat guy, right, Franky?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.31,0:10:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.81,0:10:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom started going on a rampage!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ribbit!\N--Oh, my God...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop! If you lay\None more finger on him...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.74,0:10:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.61,0:10:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...understand the pain he's feeling?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.16,0:10:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F-Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They shot him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.84,0:11:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.24,0:11:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.61,0:11:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tranquillizer bullets, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.91,0:11:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You damn fishman with superhuman\Nstrength! That serves you right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.33,0:11:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san! Why'd you do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.55,0:11:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys! What're you doing?!\NHurry up and capture them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.09,0:11:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take everyone from the ferocious\NTom's Workers company to Enies Lobby!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.35,0:11:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that Tom is such a dangerous person...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.76,0:11:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is he thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.77,0:11:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really sold his soul to pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made that many battleships and\Nwaited for an opportunity like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.36,0:12:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastards! How dare you\Ntalk like that to Tom-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.86,0:12:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.24,0:12:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.57,0:12:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judge...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.58,0:12:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.66,0:12:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll confess to the charge of\Nmaking a raid on the Judicial Ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.96,0:12:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.04,0:12:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Tom-san! Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.50,0:12:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.59,0:12:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, you stupid fishman!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.50,0:12:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who'd listen to a criminal's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.96,0:12:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your mouth shut, CP5!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is the favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.97,0:12:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can get one charge eliminated\Nfor our building the sea train...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.93,0:12:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'd like today's charge to be eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.10,0:12:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that wish is granted,\Nyou'll just go back to square one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.23,0:12:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll end up with the crime of building\Na ship for the King of the Pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.32,0:12:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which will result in the maximum penalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.41,0:12:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I prefer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.70,0:12:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About assisting that Roger guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.20,0:12:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm resolutely proud of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:12:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How selfish...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.25,0:13:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that he's proud of\Nassisting the King of the Pirates...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.59,0:13:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.59,0:13:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ferocious fishman!\N--Damn fishman!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.26,0:13:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san... Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.72,0:13:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.76,0:13:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. Don't blame yourself, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought that the Government\Nwould use force to get the blueprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.36,0:13:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was at a bit of a disadvantage\Ndue to the matter with Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.98,0:13:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, you didn't have to--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.86,0:13:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the town. Even if my charge\Ngoes back to what it was 14 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.41,0:13:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everything is different from then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.66,0:13:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This island is full of energy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.21,0:13:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.58,0:13:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.59,0:13:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can be of help to the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.05,0:13:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dream has...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.01,0:13:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...finally... begun to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.64,0:13:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.98,0:13:59.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.40,0:14:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg... Franky...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.74,0:14:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of the blueprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.82,0:14:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kokoro-san... Yokozuna...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.08,0:14:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.29,0:14:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tranquilizers have finally started working!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.21,0:14:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Capture those three culprits\Nfor the Judicial Ship raid!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.92,0:14:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.30,0:14:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh?\N--I'm changing the charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the charge of building the pirate ship\Nfor Gold Roger, King of the Pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.48,0:14:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll take shipbuilding\Nengineer Tom to Enies Lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.61,0:14:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What got into that old geezer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.36,0:14:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well. I don't have\Nbusiness with his disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.78,0:14:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Release those two disciples!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.25,0:15:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san can no longer be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.38,0:15:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's the World Government we're\Nup against, there's nothing we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.42,0:15:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bear it. Tom-san saved you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you make an enemy of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.97,0:15:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how many lives\Nyou have, it's not enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enies Lobby is the judicial island\Nowned by the Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.77,0:15:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No criminals taken there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.81,0:15:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...have ever returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea train is ready! We can take him now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.28,0:15:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.61,0:15:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kokoro-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.08,0:15:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you guys! Hurry up and take away...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.99,0:15:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.12,0:15:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this heavy, crazy fishman!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.96,0:15:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.92,0:15:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.17,0:15:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.76,0:15:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.77,0:16:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spandam-san's face got bent!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.02,0:16:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, Tom's disciple\Nstarted going on a rampage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.61,0:16:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Stop it!\N--Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.24,0:16:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Capture him! The rest of you, take Tom away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.53,0:16:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me! I won't let you take him away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.41,0:16:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're allowed to shoot him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give us Tom-san back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.29,0:16:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.84,0:16:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and run!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.55,0:16:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.60,0:16:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! He got away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.06,0:16:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never let that Cutty Flam\Nbrat get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.98,0:16:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is truly a criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.53,0:16:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once this case is over,\NI'll have him sent to the gallows!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.66,0:16:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Spandam-san!\N--What do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.41,0:17:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's Cutty Flam!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.54,0:17:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He came this far after us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.08,0:17:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's standing on the railway with some weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.88,0:17:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay there, Yokozuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.01,0:17:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.89,0:17:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he stupid or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.68,0:17:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.76,0:17:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.93,0:17:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just keep going; give him what he wants.\NDon't be concerned about him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.15,0:17:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Puffing Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.95,0:17:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you taking your creator to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.09,0:17:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit, ribbit...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.21,0:17:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you pass here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give Tom-san back to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.56,0:18:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Sea train!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.94,0:18:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Your parents abandoned you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.99,0:18:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's so funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.03,0:18:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're laughing too hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.32,0:18:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then! Come resolutely to my place!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.74,0:18:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna build ships anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.79,0:18:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't love ships that hurt\Nthe people I really care about!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.50,0:18:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Tom-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.97,0:18:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you're my goal after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I want you to come back\Nand teach me again...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.49,0:19:04.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because I want to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.87,0:19:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...build a dream ship someday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.79,0:19:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A ship that resolutely and proudly traverses
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.42,0:19:17.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even uncharted waves at edges of the earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.34,0:19:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dream ship like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.15,0:19:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What we heard about Tom\Nis that he had good skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.15,0:19:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he was a ferocious and intractable\Nfishman with superhuman strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.66,0:19:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we ask the townspeople,\Nthey just speak ambiguously.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.45,0:19:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be tough to be a disciple that has\Nto defend such a man, huh, Cutty Flam?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.87,0:19:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not even worth responding to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.38,0:19:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You Government people are all crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.50,0:19:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, more than 100 people,\Nincluding marines and officials,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.01,0:20:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were severely injured here in Water Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.05,0:20:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit behind it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.22,0:20:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had a lot to answer for, causing the\NWorld Government that much trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.19,0:20:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but since you were confirmed dead in\Nthe sea train accident on that very day,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.02,0:20:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your charge was annulled.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.53,0:20:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, we'll take you to\NEnies Lobby as a criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.49,0:20:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can take your time there\Nanswering my question...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.74,0:20:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...about the whereabouts\Nof the blueprints for Pluton.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.42,0:20:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Blueno.\N--Yeah. It just connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.22,0:20:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I reported this case to our chief,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.47,0:20:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he said he wanted to talk\Nto you right away, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.06,0:20:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your chief? Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please go ahead, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.94,0:20:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch! It's hot! It's hot! It's hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.48,0:21:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I spilled the coffee!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.69,0:21:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Stupid coffee!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.45,0:21:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.24,0:21:07.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you there...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.99,0:21:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Cutty Flam?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hm?\N--It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.08,0:21:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought you'd survived that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.54,0:21:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe, but I'm happy to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.01,0:21:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.97,0:21:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During these past eight years...\Nevery time my scars hurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.22,0:21:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was tormented by an anger that\NI couldn't take out on anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.31,0:21:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because the culprit who hurt me died!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.77,0:21:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask you again! Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.24,0:21:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.12,0:21:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the man who was from Cipher Pol No. 5
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.33,0:22:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and arrested Tom's Workers red-handed for\Nattacking the Judicial Ship eight years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.74,0:22:33.24,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We had a dream that day
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.24,0:22:38.08,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Our belief in ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.08,0:22:47.30,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,makes us able to cross the wildly surging ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:56.85,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,You're braver and more caring than anyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.85,0:23:06.86,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever depart this ship\Nand live in a different world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.86,0:23:15.66,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, we can all surely smile
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.30,0:23:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been eagerly looking forward to seeing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.09,0:23:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me... Is that you, Spanda?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.63,0:23:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"M"! You're missing the "M"! It's "Spandam"!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.68,0:23:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Lucci! Hurry up and bring\Nthem to Enies Lobby already!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.43,0:23:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Roger.\N--Hey, hold it! Let him go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.02,0:23:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What'd you say?\N--Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.02,0:23:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.23,0:23:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Truth Behind Her Betrayal!\NRobin's Sorrowful Decision!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.31,0:23:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
